# How this app was created
This is a simple app that was essentially vibe-coded using Gemini & Claude. Both were used as I am a cheapskate and did this over a few days on the free tier of both.

Here are the prompts used to create and enhance the app:

> I want a single web page to track player rotation in volleyball with 3 views:
>
>- list of players
>
>- name, player number, role (setter, outside, middle, opposite, libero)
>
>- selectable starting rotation position (I, II, III, IV, V, VI, sub, libero)
>
>- buttons to edit player
>
>- button to add player
>
>- buttons to start set
>
>- only when one player has been assigned each of the positions I to VI
>
>- button to start set with team making first serve
>
>- button to start set with team receiving first serve
>
>- Active Set view
>
>- landscape view
>
>- 3x2 grid to show the player in each position
>
>- takes most of the screen
>
>- position I is bottom right, II is top right, III top middle, IV top left, V bottom left and VI bottom middle
>
>- player number is principal information - large font
>
>- player name and position is supplementary information - small font
>
>- buttons for point won and point lost
>
>- if point won, and is a side-out (i.e. team was receiving serve) then team will make next serve and the rotation advances
>
>- player in position I moves to position VI
>
>- player in position II moves to position I
>
>- player in position III moves to position II
>
>- player in position IV moves to position III
>
>- player in position V moves to position IV
>
>- player in position VI moves to position V
>
>- if point won, and team served the point (not a sideout) then no advance of positions
>
>- if point lost, the team loses serve and receives next serve, and no advance of position
>
>- our team score
>
>- displayed top right of view
>
>- incremented when point won
>
>- their team score
>
>- displayed top left of view
>
>- incremented when point lost
